        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 7:42PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 741 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Encinal, moving northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chaparral Wildlife Management Area.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 41 and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
